<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="return-v">return <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'tɜːn/    美 /rɪ'tɜːrn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-go-come-back">1.★ <strong>回来；返回；重新出现 (go / come back)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>By the time Jack <strong>returned</strong> home / <strong>to</strong> his home from England, his son had graduated from college. <strong>from_1</strong>
当杰克从英国回到家乡的时候，他的儿子已经大学毕业了。</p><footer>2011 辽宁改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If the pain returns, make another appointment to see the doctor. 
如果疼痛反复，再预约看医生。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>归还；送回；放回：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please make sure you <strong>return</strong> the book <strong>to</strong> the library before it’s due.
请务必在到期前把书还给图书馆。</p><footer>2012 全国改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My mother’s call <strong>returned</strong> me <strong>to</strong> the real world. 
母亲的喊声把我带回到现实世界。</p><footer>2015 天津</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>(以相同的东西) 回报 / 报答：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Thanks for helping me. I’ll try to <strong>return the favour</strong> some day. 
谢谢你对我的帮助，有朝一日我会报答你的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="return-to">return to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(使) 恢复；继续做；重新做：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Even with treatment, they may never <strong>return to normal</strong>.  
即使经过治疗，他们也可能无法恢复正常。</p><footer>北师大⑦-21</footer></div></div>